<paragraph blockId="3.[677,1217,1677,1732]" lastBlockId="6.[109,649,190,311]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">
DIAGNOSIS. Most similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[940,1209,1677,1698]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dologlossum">
<emphasis box="[940,1209,1677,1698]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Bulbophyllum dologlossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differs by the acute sepals, the 4-veined (versus 1-veined) petals, the ovate-oblong lip, gradually tapering without narrowed parts towards the apex, with only 2 (versus 4) ridges on the adaxial side, and the straight stelidia.
</paragraph>
